PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/earnhub
JWT_SECRET=replace-with-a-long-random-secret

# Generic SMTP configuration. For Gmail, use an App Password, not your normal password.
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_SECURE=false
SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your-provider-app-password-or-smtp-key

# This address/domain must be verified with your email provider.
EMAIL_FROM="EarnHub <your-email@gmail.com>"
EMAIL_REPLY_TO=support@example.com

# Used only by `npm run email:check` to send a real delivery test.
EMAIL_TEST_TO=your-test-inbox@example.com

# Resend alternative:
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.resend.com
# SMTP_PORT=465
# SMTP_SECURE=true
# SMTP_USER=resend
# SMTP_PASS=re_your_api_key
# EMAIL_FROM="EarnHub <verify@your-verified-domain.com>"

The OTP email is not being delivered in my MERN application.

Please analyze and fix the complete email OTP flow.

Requirements:

* Check the frontend registration flow and confirm that clicking the "Create My Account" button triggers the OTP request.
* Verify that the backend API receives the request and generates the OTP correctly.
* Check whether the OTP is being saved or cached properly for verification.
* Verify the email sending logic and identify why emails are not being delivered.
* Check SMTP or email provider configuration and report any missing environment variables.
* If SMTP credentials are missing, clearly specify which variables need to be added to `backend/.env`.
* Add detailed logging for OTP generation, email sending, and delivery failures.
* Ensure that errors are returned to the frontend instead of failing silently.
* After I add the required credentials, run a real email delivery test using a test email address and confirm that the OTP email arrives successfully.
* Show all files modified and explain every change made.
* Do not expose or print sensitive credentials such as passwords or API keys.


